Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to turn. Clay near fine light brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 71, 9. Name Astymedes. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 053.52
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0729)
